{
  "texts": [
    "Dense retrievers employ dual-encoders to generate dense vector representations of text for more accurate semantic matching.",
    "Consequently, dense retrievers are considered more suitable for retrieval-augmented applications.",
    "Some techniques like vector quantization [25,47] and embedding optimization [48] also improves the efficiency of dense retrievers.",
    "Common dense retrievers include DPR [20], ANCE [49] and Contriever [13].",
    "Specifically, DPR [20] is trained with supervised learning on question-answer pairs, and focuses on extracting relevant passages by analyzing the semantic content of both questions and answers."
  ]
}